const obsidian_docs = [{
    "id": "coronation",
    "fileName": "0 First Coronation.md",
    "year": 0,
    "title": "First Coronation",
    "content": "Estin-Orvet was crowned as Great Uniter and [[ruler-f-1]] of [[Kingdom]].\n\nWith the exile of Feif and his followers to the Field of Beasts, the kingdom is safe and [[kingdom citizen]] will prosper.\n\nOrvet, in her wisdom, has ushered in the first Era of a United [[Kingdom]]: The era of Temperance."
}, {
    "id": "concord",
    "fileName": "0 Founding Concord.md",
    "year": 0,
    "title": "Founding Concord",
    "content": "To promote peace amongst the three great families, a joint royal family will be founded. Estin-[[family]] and Tamoth-[[family]] will be the [[ruler-f-1]] and [[ruler-consort-m]], while Yoret-[[family]] will provide the [[ruler-consort]] to the first heir."
}, {
    "id": "succession",
    "fileName": "0 Rules of Succession.md",
    "year": 0,
    "title": "Rules of Succession",
    "content": "When the current [[ruler]] dies or is no longer able to perform their duties, their youngest [[child]] who has a [[spouse]] or is betrothed and has passed their [[Coming of Age Trial]] is heir and shall become [[ruler]]. If they do not have a [[child]] that is a suitable heir, then succession passes to their youngest [[sibling-older]]."
}, {
    "id": "rules",
    "fileName": "1 Rules of living in Trevosa.md",
    "year": 1,
    "title": "Rules of living in Trevosa",
    "content": "[[1]] -- Respect the authority of the [[ruler]].\n[[2]] -- Stay out of the rain.\n[[3]] -- Never linger in the Open.\n[[4]] -- Keep your voice measured in Hollow Places.\n[[5]] -- Gather provisions for times of drought.\n[[6]] -- Mark your trails down unfamiliar paths.\n[[7]] -- Surround yourself with those you trust.\n[[8]] -- Only [[idiot]] sleep without an assigned Watcher.\n[[9]] -- Do not explore past the Great Threshold.\n[[10]] -- Always remember, this world is not our own."
}, {
    "id": "calserem",
    "fileName": "10 First Calserem.md",
    "year": 10,
    "title": "First Calserem",
    "content": "Orvet-[[ruler-f-1]] decreed that Oleel of Yoret-[[family]] shall be the [[godparent-m]] of her [[child]], Basheel, Corvin, and heir Taal. As [[godparent-m]] Oleel shall be a protector and [[auncle-m-older]] if not by blood, to the three.\n\nConsidering Oleel's [[child-f-1]] Celdei and her close friendship with Corvin, the story of Yoret-[[family]] will be intertwined with the future of [[Kingdom]] for generations to come."
}, {
    "id": "lemot-last-words",
    "fileName": "110 Yoret-Lemot's Last Words.md",
    "year": 110,
    "title": "Yoret-Lemot's Last Words",
    "content": "Sartina, I will not live to see Yoret-[[family]] restored to be [[ruler]].\n\nLive well, regardless. May you find a [[spouse-m]], [[spouse-f]], or [[spouse-nb]] that mixes and rises with you, like the smoke of a candle.\n\nTrust in the goodness of all [[Giant]] and heed their omens.\n\nLet it be written that I was vanquished in battle, but never in spirit."
}, {
    "id": "proclamation",
    "fileName": "155 Proclamation of a New Era.md",
    "year": 155,
    "title": "Proclamation of a New Era",
    "content": "I, Tamoth-Nyreen-[[ruler-nb-5]], [[child]] of Tamoth-Nolveth-[[ruler-m-4]] and [[grandchild]] of Tamoth-Telai, give the following decree.\n\nMy [[parent-m]] harnessed the power of [[ant]] to retake the kingdom.\n\nWe shall push further. We will train the [[fly]] above us to fight and [[serpent]] below us to forage. We will harness beasts and launch [[Kingdom]] into a new era!"
}, {
    "id": "restoration",
    "fileName": "161 The Restoration.md",
    "year": 161,
    "title": "The Restoration",
    "content": "After the Usurpation by The Heir of Beasts, the crown passed to his [[child]], Tamoth-Nyreen-[[ruler-nb-5]]. They had a great vision for [[Kingdom]], but their ideas were so wildly impractical and caused some much chaos that they were deposed after only a few seasons. Every [[family]] of [[Kingdom]], their own included, colluded for them to be exiled.\n\nEchoing the Founding, Estin-Amath was declared [[ruler-f-6]], and Yoret-Yaron as [[ruler-consort-m]]. Their return to tradition was blessed, and the Era of Plenty began."
}, {
    "id": "scouting-report",
    "fileName": "163 Scouting Report.md",
    "year": 163,
    "title": "Scouting Report",
    "content": "Yoret-Sartina, [[child-f]] of Yoret-Lemot and Yoret-Tyreil, has found a huge supply of food. The new [[Giant]]-[[family]] grants us bread and other staples near the Hollow Place. She is The Wayward no longer.\n\nThe food is very far from our homes, so a council should be called to determine the best plan of action."
}, {
    "id": "transit-solution",
    "fileName": "166 Transit Solution Report.md",
    "year": 166,
    "title": "Transit Solution Report",
    "content": "As requested in royal directive [[9]], a [[mouse]] has been harnessed to provide rapid transportation as a mount. This has allowed mounted gatherers to bring back much greater quantities of food than we have seen prior to this era.\n\nThe [[mouse]] is a mostly docile beast, though stepping on its thin, bald tail can cause it to lash out. The Quartermaster may be young, but has instituted a rigorous training program to train couriers in [[mouse]] riding and care. This gives us much better access to the food supplies his [[parent-f]] so famously found."
}, {
    "id": "security-check",
    "fileName": "177 Security check.md",
    "year": 177,
    "title": "Security check",
    "content": "Security Minister,\n\nWhile the Tamoth-[[family]] was behind the [[ant]] war and following disasters, not all of them were complicit. Like all large [[family]], there are many branches, and some chose to stay out of the conflict, or side against the main branch.\n\nTamoth-Narset comes from one of these branches. As far as well can tell, she chose to live on the outskirts and stay out of factional politics for generations. Narset herself is eccentric compared to most nobles, choosing to sew her own clothes even though she can easily pay for a tailor. However, she shows no sign or links to any potential rebellion, so the guards have no objection to her [[marriage]] to Yoret-Morfal.\n\n-Guard, Division 4 Scribe"
}, {
    "id": "performance-eval",
    "fileName": "178 Performance Evaluation.md",
    "year": 178,
    "title": "Performance Evaluation",
    "content": "Your Royal Highness, Estin-Amath-[[ruler-f-6]],\n\nI was initially skeptical of appointing your [[child-m-2]]'s [[spouse-f]]'s [[sibling-m-younger]] as head of couriers. Yoret-Morfal has just recently passed his [[Coming of Age Trial]], and I thought the role would be too much for someone without extensive experience. I am very glad to have been incorrect.\n\nThe [[mouse]] courier program has been successful beyond any reasonable expectation, in no small part due to Morfal's diligence in training. The Quartermaster title, bestowed for his services, no longer seems enough. Maybe the throne can bestow additional gifts during his upcoming [[marriage]] to Tamoth-Narset.\n\n-- Minister of Supply and Provisions"
}, {
    "id": "tutoring",
    "fileName": "182 Tutoring notes.md",
    "year": 182,
    "title": "Tutoring notes",
    "content": "Estin-Aarna is sweet and energetic but an unfocused student. She is much more at home outside, chasing [[fly]]. She attempts to be studious, but she clearly lacks the focus for true scholarly greatness.\n\nHer [[sibling-m-younger]] Estin-Roal is much more academic, and loves to challenge what he reads. While this can be tiresome during lessons, I believe it will make him an excellent [[ruler]] and administrator."
}, {
    "id": "note-to-roal",
    "fileName": "195 Note to my Oloth-obrao.md",
    "year": 195,
    "title": "Note to my Oloth-obrao",
    "content": "Dearest Roal,\n\nWith your upcoming [[marriage]] to Soleel, I thought I would offer you some perspective from my old age.\n\nBefore the Era of Plenty, some important [[marriage]] took place in troubled times. Your [[parent-f]] [[ruler-f-6]] never had a true [[festival-marriage]]. Instead she had a small [[festival]] with only their closest [[family]] in attendance. I remember how Yaron stood a full head above everyone else. He was hard to miss!\n\nRemember that you can find joy in any occasion. Your [[parent-f]] had no idea what life had in store for her, and now she's restored [[Kingdom]] to its former glory."
}, {
    "id": "realms",
    "fileName": "2 The Three Realms.md",
    "year": 2,
    "title": "The Three Realms",
    "content": "Seasons before the unification of [[Kingdom]], the three [[family]] each had their own domain.\n\nEstin-[[family]]:\nThe Open and Hollow Places.\n\nYoret-[[family]]:\nThe Crevices and Pathways.\n\nTamoth-[[family]]:\nThe Edge of the Kingdom, bordering the Field of Beasts.\n\nTamoth-Feif's exile, in this sense, is almost a return home."
}, {
    "id": "aarna-to-soleel",
    "fileName": "212 Personal note.md",
    "year": 212,
    "title": "Personal note",
    "content": "Yoret-Soleel-[[ruler-consort-f]], [[spouse-f]] of my [[sibling-m-younger]], don't worry about feeling lost. Each of our [[sibling-younger]] are shining so brightly that there is no way for us to eclipse them. Focus instead of what you want. I have embraced my role as the Royal Rider, and devote my energy to making sure everyone who wants to can ride [[mouse]] and venture forth into the world.\n\nI have heard your gifts of song, and some in the palace refer to you as one of the singing great birds. Embrace your talents and show us what you can do, unburdened by conventional expectations.\n\n-- Estin-Aarna"
}, {
    "id": "sartina-obituary",
    "fileName": "221 Royal Varelen Obituary.md",
    "year": 221,
    "title": "Royal Varelen Obituary",
    "content": "We mourn the death of Yoret-Sartina, [[parent-f]] of Yoret-Soleel-[[ruler-consort-f]]. After completing her [[Coming of Age Trial]] near the end of the [[ant]] war, she split from her [[parent-m]] when he was forced into exile by the usurpation of Heir of Beasts. Her [[festival-marriage]] was performed in secret so as not to attract the attention of [[ruler-m-4]], and she and her [[family]] lived on the periphery, scouting the edges of [[Kingdom]].\n\nIn 161, she discovered a new foraging ground that led to the era of plenty. Her [[child-m-2]] went on to develop the [[mouse]] transit solution that made it even more accessible. Her [[child]] remember her warmly, and her [[grandchild]] will miss her."
}, {
    "id": "baby-announcement",
    "fileName": "236 Royal Baby Announcement.md",
    "year": 236,
    "title": "Royal Baby Announcement",
    "content": "My [[child-m]] Yoret-Oreleth and his [[spouse-f]] welcome their first [[child]] today, a beautiful [[child-m]] called Ludir. We and the [[kingdom citizen]] wish them great health on the start of their journey as [[parent-m]] and [[parent-f]]!\n\nEstin-Roal-[[ruler-m-7]]"
}, {
    "id": "great-expectations",
    "fileName": "239 Great Expectations.md",
    "year": 239,
    "title": "Great Expectations",
    "content": "Yoret-Oreleth will ascend to the throne with great hopes for his reign. After his [[grandparent-f]] The Restorer, and his [[parent-m]] The Prosperous, the [[kingdom citizen]] expect great things from him. All eyes now follow the soon-to-be [[ruler-m-8]]."
}, {
    "id": "monster",
    "fileName": "243 The Monster.md",
    "year": 243,
    "title": "The Monster",
    "content": "All the reports from yesterday's attack are finally in, and here is the synthesized summary.\n\nIn the early afternoon, the second patrol left as normal to head to the foraging grounds. No incidents occurred while traveling through Crevices, but a second after we emerged into the Hollow Place, the team was attacked by a massive monster. It leapt upon us from above, grabbing one of the pack [[mouse]] and bounding away before we could even think. The other [[mouse]] bolted back immediately, with its rider holding on for dear life.\n\nNo [[kingdom citizen]] was hurt. We are calling it the [[cat]], and we need to decide what to do next.\n\n-Guard Office Clerk"
}, {
    "id": "great-passage",
    "fileName": "250 The Great Oltev Proposal.md",
    "year": 250,
    "title": "The Great Oltev Proposal",
    "content": "Today, the only access to the fertile foraging ground requires moving long distances through open spaces, yet the arrival of the [[cat]] stops us from using [[mouse]] to carry loads across.\n\nI propose we open a new covered route to the foraging ground. An extensive survey is needed, but early examination shows that we could tunnel beneath the massive caverns of the [[Giant]] to reach an area very near the foraging grounds, all out of reach of the [[cat]]. It's a project on a scale the [[kingdom citizen]] have never attempted, but it may be our best chance.\n\n-- Tamoth-Ervala"
}, {
    "id": "plea-from-cyno",
    "fileName": "254 A Plea from the Cyno.md",
    "year": 254,
    "title": "A Plea from the Cyno",
    "content": "Yoret-Eirlov, my far distant relative.\n\nI am asking you to put your dream on hold. I know there's no greater sacrifice to ask of someone, but we all need The Great [[Passage]] to work. It's the only way we have found to avert a famine before we run out of stockpiled food.\n\nYour [[spouse-f]] Tamoth-Ervala spends every waking minute on excavations, to the point she is being named after the Earth for living underground. Do everything you can to support her in this. We are all counting on you two.\n\nYoret-Oreleth-[[ruler-m-8]]"
}, {
    "id": "basheel-speech",
    "fileName": "26 Basheel's Speech.md",
    "year": 26,
    "title": "Basheel's Speech",
    "content": "On this joyous day of your [[festival-marriage]], allow me to say a few words to Corvin's new [[spouse-f]].\n\nCeldei, I have never heard you speak ill of my [[sibling-m-younger]]. I have barely heard you speak at all. You do seem enamored with Corvin's beauty, nearly as much as he is. That seems an excellent foundation for a long and fruitful relationship.\n\nI wish you both get exactly what you deserve."
}, {
    "id": "funeral-diary",
    "fileName": "260 Funeral Diary Entry.md",
    "year": 260,
    "title": "Funeral Diary Entry",
    "content": "Today was the funeral for [[parent-f]]. She never recovered after pushing so hard to finish The Great [[Passage]]. She gave it everything, and had nothing left for [[parent-m]] and I. After hearing tales of her [[Coming of Age Trial]], I wanted her to see me complete mine, but that is no longer to be.\n\nI supposed that everyone at the funeral would honor her, but I didn't expect the [[ruler-m-8]] and his [[family]] to be there. Estin-Lysna-[[ruler-consort-f]] pulled me aside and spoke to me. She apologized for everything that our family had to sacrifice for everyone else, and vowed that would not continue. After [[parent-m]] had his wings clipped by this project, she wants to make sure I can pursue my dream - she even offered to be my [[godparent-f]]. I can see why she was called The Nurse back during the battle against the [[cat]]. I promised I will speak with her when I have a better idea of where I want to go in life."
}, {
    "id": "archive-created",
    "fileName": "27 Archive Created.md",
    "year": 27,
    "title": "Archive Created",
    "content": "Orvet-[[ruler-f-1]] and Beseet-[[ruler-consort-m]] decreed the creation of the [[royal archives]]. All important writings, decrees, and prophecies of all [[ruler]] of [[Kingdom]] shall be recorded for future generations, that all may reflect upon the glory and dignity of those who have come before. The collection will be managed by Oleel the Curator, [[godparent-m]] to the [[child]] of Orvet and Beseet, who has a keen interest in preserving historic writings."
}, {
    "id": "stalwart-1",
    "fileName": "270 The Reign of the Stalwart pt. 1.md",
    "year": 270,
    "title": "The Reign of the Stalwart pt. 1",
    "content": "The [[ruler-m-8]] earned his moniker of The Stalwart by steering the [[Kingdom]] through the biggest and longest crisis since the [[ant]] war. This crisis was caused by the appearance of the [[cat]] and the severing of the courier line through the Hollow Place.\n\nWe immediately learned that the beast could not stay away from our [[mouse]]. When our brave warriors tried to protect the [[mouse]], the [[cat]] swatted them away with ease. This caused such devastation that attempts to confront the [[cat]] were quickly abandoned. Lysna-[[ruler-consort-f]] led the efforts to care for the wounded, leading to her moniker, The Nurse."
}, {
    "id": "stalwart-2",
    "fileName": "271 The Reign of the Stalwart pt. 2.md",
    "year": 271,
    "title": "The Reign of the Stalwart pt. 2",
    "content": "Knowing the severity of the situation, the [[ruler-m-8]] directed [[kingdom citizen]] to find different sources of food. Some marginal areas were able to be cultivated, but the largest efforts went into scouting for places to forage far away from the [[cat]] and the Hollow Place. Nothing of note was discovered.\n\nThe project that led to relief was The Great [[Passage]]. The [[mouse]] cannot cross the Hollow Place, so we created closed spaces. As decreed by the [[ruler-m-8]], Yoret-Eirlov set aside his inventions that were intended to take to the air, and instead spent seven seasons working beside Tamoth-Ervala to build lifts and tunnel a great distance. The [[Passage]] is longer than previous routes, but contains nothing more dangerous than the occasional eyeless [[worm]] crawling through the tunnel. We no longer need fear losing access to food."
}, {
    "id": "letter-to-talai",
    "fileName": "275 Letter to Talai.md",
    "year": 275,
    "title": "Letter to Talai",
    "content": "Dear [[parent-f]],\n\nI'm writing to let you know that Lonara and I had a [[festival-marriage]] yesterday. It's been [[4]] seasons since Lonara completed her [[Coming of Age Trial]] and we refuse to wait for your blessing any longer. Lysna-[[ruler-consort-f]] was generous enough to take on the role during the [[festival]] instead.\n\nI'll repeat again that it's been three generations since the Restoration, and there's no question of Tamoth-[[family]]'s loyalty to [[Kingdom]]. Lonara in particular is the [[grandchild-f]] of The Quartermaster, whose lineage goes all the way back to the [[sibling-m-older]] of the [[ruler-f-2]].\n\nEven if none of that were true, it should be enough that Lonara is dedicated, hardworking, and creative, and I love her.\n\nI trust you will come to terms with this,\nYour [[child-m]],\nYoret-Temig"
}, {
    "id": "scepter-crisis",
    "fileName": "277 The Scepter Crisis.md",
    "year": 277,
    "title": "The Scepter Crisis",
    "content": "After the success of The Great [[Passage]], efforts were made to explore other deep chasms. In the depths of one such chasm, in a den of [[worm]], the surveyors found the royal scepter that was forged for the [[ruler-f-1]] but disappeared during the War of [[ant]]. We curators were ecstatic at the find, and spent an entire season cleaning and restoring it.\n\nInscribed on the scepter are the words: \"The Concord secures the rule of the rightful [[ruler]]\". Its return prompted the original Founding Concord and Rules of Succession to be fetched from the [[royal archives]], which led to chaos in the court upon the determination that no [[ruler]] since the [[ruler-m-3]] has been a legitimate descendant and heir of the [[ruler-f-1]], including the Restorer and her line.\n\nThe [[ruler-m-8]] stood firm, decreeing that for the stability of [[Kingdom]], his line will continue to rule. Only if there is no suitable heir will the crown and scepter be returned to the line of the [[ruler-f-1]]."
}, {
    "id": "ode-to-oleel",
    "fileName": "28 Ode to the Curator.md",
    "year": 28,
    "title": "Ode to the Curator",
    "content": "The First Curator:\n\n[[parent-m]] to a [[child-f-1]] and [[godparent-m]] to three,\nNe'er a [[ruler]] but they he directed.\n[[Kingdom]] shall forever in his debt be,\nHis words shall be recalled and collected.\n\n[From the desk of Yoret-Oleel]"
}, {
    "id": "letter-to-exile",
    "fileName": "3 Letter to the Exile.md",
    "year": 3,
    "title": "Letter to the Exile",
    "content": "No, I have not forgotten you, [[sibling-m-younger]]. I remember your ambition. I remember your bitterness. I remember your cruelty.\n\nI have a new title to live up to, and it is incompatible with what our family has stood for.\n\nI hope, if you are not stepped on by a [[Giant]], that the Field of Beasts will, with time, teach you and my former kin humility.\n\n-- Beseet"
}, {
    "id": "threatening-note",
    "fileName": "3 Threatening Note.md",
    "year": 3,
    "title": "Threatening Note",
    "content": "Beseet, [[sibling-m-older]], have you forgotten about me already?\n\nI hear the music and din of your nightly [[festival]] - so much for your [[spouse-f]] and her \"era of temperance\".\n\nYes, even in the Field of Beasts of my exile. I can hear them. I am not so far away as you think. At night, when the [[Giant]] go up to the heights, I'm closer than they are.\n\nYou may have forgotten your kin at your [[marriage]] to Orvet-[[ruler-f-1]], but we have not forgotten about you.\n\nI vow, so long as a true member of Tamoth-[[family]] is breathing, [[Kingdom]] will not be safe."
}, {
    "id": "passive-aggressive",
    "fileName": "33 Passive-aggressive Letter.md",
    "year": 33,
    "title": "Passive-aggressive Letter",
    "content": "To Basheel -\n\nYour absence at my [[festival-marriage]] was much appreciated.\n\nTruly.\n\nWho in [[Kingdom]] will wonder why the [[child-f-1]] of Orvet-[[ruler-f-1]] was missing from Taal and Lemal's [[festival-marriage]]? Surely, no one. No one will ask why Basheel was off on an expedition, chasing [[fly]], or whatever it is you do.\n\nYes, I will be [[ruler-f-2]] someday. It was not up to me. These are the rules of succession. Will you let your bitterness taint our bloodline?\n\nYour [[sibling-f-younger]],\nTaal"
}, {
    "id": "basheel-journal",
    "fileName": "37 Basheel's Journal on the Exile Telai.md",
    "year": 37,
    "title": "Basheel's Journal on the Exile Telai",
    "content": "I will record her name here in my journal:\n\nTamoth-Telai.\n\nOn my expedition across the arid lands, I met the most unlikely of travelers: my [[parent-m]]'s [[nibling-f]] on an expedition of her own. Still the [[child-f-1]] of a traitor and an exile, her story of our [[family]] was twisted and poisoned. But regardless of the lies she had been taught, she had a kind heart and spoke of contentment with her life in the Field of Beasts. She was not interested in reconciliation, only the rations I had available to trade.\n\nPerhaps she will not be remembered in our [[royal archives]], but she lives a live so much simpler than my own. I envy her: I would rather be forgotten to history than beholden to its expectations.\n\nI pray all the exiles will likewise be complacent with their lot in life."
}, {
    "id": "lemot-born",
    "fileName": "42 Yoret-Lemot is Born.md",
    "year": 42,
    "title": "Yoret-Lemot is Born",
    "content": "Yoret-Celdei and Estin-Corvin welcome their long-awaited [[child-m]] to their [[family]].\n\nNamed Yoret-Lemot, he is the first [[child]] born of this generation. Estin-Basheel was named [[godparent-f]].\n\nBoth Estin-Basheel and her [[sibling-f-younger]] Estin-Taal-[[ruler-f-2]] congratulated the couple and were eager to meet their [[nibling-m]]."
}, {
    "id": "adopted-heir",
    "fileName": "44 The Adopted Heir.md",
    "year": 44,
    "title": "The Adopted Heir",
    "content": "Estin-Taal-[[ruler-f-2]] and her [[spouse-m]] Lemal decree to all the kingdom their full intent to name their [[child-f-1]] Caldosa as [[ruler-f-3]] of [[Kingdom]] when she comes of age and completes her [[Coming of Age Trial]].\n\nThose who whisper of her \"tainted blood\" as an outsider are [[enemy]] to all of the kingdom and risk severe penalty."
}, {
    "id": "heir-rejection",
    "fileName": "68 Rejection of Adopted Heir.md",
    "year": 68,
    "title": "Rejection of Adopted Heir",
    "content": "The fact of the matter, dear [[sibling-f-younger]], is [[kingdom citizen]] do not respect your [[child-f-1]] Caldosa. What's more, I may call her [[nibling-f]], but she is not of our blood, and succession rules are not merely suggestions.\n\nI have an heir. You do not have a suitable heir.\n\nYou and I know that Lemot must be the [[ruler-m-3]] to maintain order. Save your [[family]] dishonor and cease fighting against it.\n\n-- Estin-Corvin"
}, {
    "id": "death-of-taal",
    "fileName": "72 The Death of Estin-Taal.md",
    "year": 72,
    "title": "The Death of Estin-Taal",
    "content": "In a most tragic accident, while hunting furry [[mouse]] in the Crevices, a vicious fanged [[serpent]] attacked and killed the [[ruler-f-2]].\n\nEstin-Taal will be remembered as a caring [[parent-f]] to all of [[Kingdom]].\n\nEstin-Corvin, per the laws of succession, would be [[ruler-m-3]], but has announced that instead, he will host the [[festival-coronation]] in one season's time, with his [[child-m-1]] Yoret-Lemot declared [[ruler-m-3]] following his [[marriage]] to Yoret-Tyreil."
}, {
    "id": "cyno-yen",
    "fileName": "74 The Cyno-yen.md",
    "year": 74,
    "title": "The Cyno-yen",
    "content": "The 74th season began with both a [[festival-marriage]] and [[festival-coronation]]. Yoret-Lemot, now Yoret-Lemot-[[ruler-m-3]] took Yoret-Tyreil, now Yoret-Tyreil-[[ruler-consort]], to be his [[spouse-nb]].\n\nMay he reign with the temperance of his [[grandparent-f]] and the peaceableness of his [[grandparent-m]]. May his reign be long!"
}, {
    "id": "prophecy",
    "fileName": "83 Prophecy.md",
    "year": 83,
    "title": "Prophecy",
    "content": "Yoret-Tyreil-[[ruler-consort]], The Seer, and [[spouse]] of Yoret-Lemot-[[ruler-m-3]], offered the following powerful interpretation of a colorful omen on a line flying in the distant sky:\n\n\"The Exiles will return when one of our own turns [[enemy]]. One we call [[family]] will open the Great Threshold and devastation will follow.\""
}, {
    "id": "rumors",
    "fileName": "85 Letter about Rumors.md",
    "year": 85,
    "title": "Letter about Rumors",
    "content": "Celdei,\n\nI am not a [[idiot]]. I know where these rumors about me originated.\n\nYour outward visage of a kind and quiet [[parent-f]] is as flimsy as your [[spouse-m]]'s vain beauty.\n\nIn reality, he is insecure. And you are a [[serpent]].\n\nMy days of exploration have passed, and yet, the rumblings of my disloyalty continue. They say I might open the Great Threshold at any moment.\n\nNo, I am not \"friends\" with exiles. If you fear a betrayal at the hands of [[family]], I suggest you look elsewhere.\n\n--Basheel"
}, {
    "id": "catalog",
    "fileName": "86 Catalog of Beasts.md",
    "year": 86,
    "title": "Catalog of Beasts",
    "content": "A catalog of beasts by Tamoth-Nolveth:\n\n[[fly]] -- A speedy creature with wings. Mostly harmless, but will eat food that is not protected.\n[[worm]] -- Digs blindly in the earth. Useless.\n[[mouse]] -- Size of a [[kingdom citizen]], soft fur, very clever. There is perhaps an opportunity to use these someday...\n[[serpent]] -- No arms or legs. Only spine, scales, and teeth. Too large and dangerous.\n\n[[ant]] -- Small but unflinching, with great strength and many legs. Capable of great coordination. With our training, I believe these will be the key to our retaking [[Kingdom]]."
}, {
    "id": "opening",
    "fileName": "87 The Opening.md",
    "year": 87,
    "title": "The Opening",
    "content": "The Great Threshold is open. Take your [[ant]] army and march into the kingdom. Claim the title of [[ruler-m-4]]. So long as my [[child-f-1]] becomes [[ruler-consort-f]], I welcome the invasion.\n\nNo matter what [[kingdom citizen]] say of her blood, she is my heart. And I will see her rule."
}, {
    "id": "shout-of-war",
    "fileName": "88 The Shout of War.md",
    "year": 88,
    "title": "The Shout of War",
    "content": "The shouted words which echoed the start of a violent new era:\n\nLemot-[[ruler-m-3]], Tyreil-[[ruler-consort]]! The Great Threshold has been opened, and the Tamoth-[[enemy]] march forward!"
}, {
    "id": "war-began",
    "fileName": "88 The War Began.md",
    "year": 88,
    "title": "The War Began",
    "content": "In the 88th season, Tamoth-Nolveth, the [[grandchild-m]] of Tamoth-Feif, returned from exile.\n\nWith an army of mighty many-legged [[ant]], he marched through the Great Threshold, opened by someone inside the kingdom, and began a brutal assault.\n\nBeasts have never been harnessed for warfare, but Nolveth, a [[child-m-1]] of exile, was Heir of Beasts."
}, {
    "id": "war-sickness",
    "fileName": "90 War and Sickness.md",
    "year": 90,
    "title": "War and Sickness",
    "content": "In season 90, amidst the devastation of the [[ant]] War, Yoret-Tyreil-[[ruler-consort]] came down with a sickness that took their life.\n\nTheir last interpretation of an [[Giant]] omen was as follows:\n\n\"The [[grandchild-m]] of Exiles will win and reign, but their [[child]] someday will lose.\"\n\nTheir prophecy gave little comfort to their [[spouse-m]] the [[ruler-m-3]] or their [[child-f]] Yoret-Sartina."
}, {
    "id": "war-crowned",
    "fileName": "95 The War-Crowned Cyno.md",
    "year": 95,
    "title": "The War-Crowned Cyno",
    "content": "Tamoth-Nolveth, conquerer of [[Kingdom]] and Heir of Beasts, was officially recognized as [[ruler-m-4]] by Estin-[[family]] and Yoret-[[family]] in season 95. In the same season, Tamoth-Nolveth-[[ruler-m-4]] announced his intent to name Caldosa as his [[spouse-f]] and [[ruler-consort-f]]. Her family connections, even though they are adoptive rather than blood, lent validity to his reign over [[Kingdom]].\n\nCaldosa's [[parent-m]], Yoret-Lemal, expressed that Estin-Taal-[[ruler-f-2]] would be pleased to see her [[child-f]] as a ruler."
}];

const obsidian_key_docs = {
    "end": {
        "id": "end",
        "key": "end",
        "fileName": "_end Final Note.md",
        "year": null,
        "title": "Final Note",
        "content": "Thank you, [[Giant]]. Although this is not the answer that I or my talo would have wished, without a [[spouse]] I cannot claim the crown or scepter. Lonara-[[ruler-f-9]] will be a dedicated ruler and bring stability to [[Kingdom]].\n\nAlthough the [[kingdom citizen]] are beneath you in every sense, your care for our history is apparent. Thank you.\n\nI have one last request:\nPlease, watch where you tread-- and keep your furry [[cat]] well fed.\n\nLudir"
    },
    "intro": {
        "id": "intro",
        "key": "intro",
        "fileName": "_intro Note to Translator.md",
        "year": null,
        "title": "Note to Translator",
        "content": "This collection of peculiar documents appears to be the records of a kingdom called [[Kingdom]]. The material has been translated where possible, but some cultural terms could not been translated.\n\nTry searching foreign terms or names in order to fill in the family tree. As you investigate these documents, keep in mind a larger question: who are these people and where do they come from?"
    },
    "start": {
        "id": "signal",
        "key": "start",
        "fileName": "_start The Signal.md",
        "year": null,
        "title": "The Signal",
        "content": "To the great [[Giant]] -\n\nI am Ludir, [[child-m-1]] of Oreleth-[[ruler-m-8]] of [[Kingdom]].\n\nIf this signal has reached you, the situation is dire. The dreadful [[cat]] lies in wait to destroy, and [[kingdom citizen]] look to the [[Giant]] for an omen: who is the true heir?\n\nBut a decision should never be made in ignorance, even for a [[Giant]]. I have sent you all of the [[royal archives]]. Please, learn of our [[family]] all the way back to Estin-Orvet-[[ruler-f-1]], learn the rules of succession, and let your voice silence the [[enemy]] who wish for chaos.\n\nLet your omen bring us peace."
    }
};

